#
# Local MinerU sidecar helper configuration.
#
# This file is consumed by scripts/mineru/install.sh and scripts/mineru/api.sh.
# It is not DlightRAG runtime config. Edit config.yaml for parser_sidecars.*.
#
# Setup:
#   cp .env.mineru.example .env.mineru
#   make mineru-install
#   make mineru-api

# Dedicated MinerU service virtualenv.
MINERU_SERVICE_VENV=.venv-mineru

# MinerU Python extras passed to: uv pip install -U "mineru[$MINERU_INSTALL_EXTRAS]".
# When unset, the installer defaults to core,mlx on Apple Silicon and core
# elsewhere. This template optimizes for local Apple Silicon development.
MINERU_INSTALL_EXTRAS=core,mlx

# Cross-platform CPU default:
# MINERU_INSTALL_EXTRAS=core

# GPU/server variants, when supported by the target MinerU release:
# MINERU_INSTALL_EXTRAS=core,vllm
# MINERU_INSTALL_EXTRAS=core,lmdeploy

# ── MinerU Python interpreter ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# MinerU supports CPython 3.10-3.13 only. scripts/mineru/install.sh pins the
# sidecar venv to this interpreter (uv downloads it if missing), so a host whose
# default python is 3.14+ still resolves wheels (onnxruntime ships no cp314
# build). Set a different supported version here to override.
MINERU_PYTHON=3.13

# ── MinerU version floor ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DlightRAG requires MinerU 3.4.4 or newer. scripts/mineru/install.sh reads this
# key and installs:
#   uv pip install -U "mineru[$MINERU_INSTALL_EXTRAS]>=$MINERU_MIN_VERSION"
# so fresh installs and `-U` upgrades always land on 3.4.4 and onward. Raise this
# floor to require a newer baseline. (When unset, the installer defaults to 3.4.4.)
MINERU_MIN_VERSION=3.4.4

# Optional exact pin for reproducible installs. When set, it overrides the floor
# above and installs that precise release instead:
#   uv pip install -U "mineru[$MINERU_INSTALL_EXTRAS]==$MINERU_VERSION"
# MINERU_VERSION=3.4.4

# Local API bind address. config.yaml defaults parser_sidecars.mineru.local_endpoint
# to http://127.0.0.1:8210, so keep these aligned unless you also update config.yaml.
MINERU_API_HOST=127.0.0.1
MINERU_API_PORT=8210

# ── MinerU Gradio WebUI (optional, on by default) ─────────────────────────
# `make mineru-service-*` brings up the Gradio WebUI alongside the API as a
# second background agent, so one command starts both. The WebUI is a thin front
# end: it REUSES the API backend above, so it never loads a second copy of the
# models — the extra cost is one lightweight process plus this port. Open it at
# http://127.0.0.1:7860 after `make mineru-service-start`.
#
# It is a MinerU diagnostic tool (preview how a document parses), not a DlightRAG
# surface, and it shares the API's single serial parse lane — parsing in the
# WebUI and a live DlightRAG ingest take turns rather than run in parallel.
#
# SECURITY: the WebUI has NO authentication. Keep MINERU_GRADIO_HOST on loopback
# (127.0.0.1); only use 0.0.0.0 on a trusted network you accept exposing it to.
MINERU_GRADIO_HOST=127.0.0.1
MINERU_GRADIO_PORT=7860

# Set to false to manage ONLY the API backend (no WebUI) — e.g. headless hosts.
# MINERU_GRADIO_ENABLE=false

# Override the API URL the WebUI calls. Defaults to http://MINERU_API_HOST:PORT
# (0.0.0.0 is rewritten to 127.0.0.1 for the loopback call).
# MINERU_GRADIO_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8210

# ── Title-level correction (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────
# MinerU uses an external LLM to correct the title hierarchy of parsed output.
# Enabling this improves the quality of paragraph-semantic chunking, which
# depends on accurate title structure for document segmentation.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Uncomment the lines below and fill in your LLM endpoint credentials.
#   2. Run:  make mineru-title-aided
#   3. This writes ~/mineru.json (outside the repo — never committed).
#   4. Restart the MinerU sidecar:  make mineru-api
#
# The LLM only processes title metadata (text + font size + page number),
# never document content.  Cost is negligible (~a few tokens per document).

# MINERU_TITLE_AIDED_ENABLE=true
# MINERU_TITLE_AIDED_API_KEY=sk-...
# MINERU_TITLE_AIDED_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com
# MINERU_TITLE_AIDED_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash
# MINERU_TITLE_AIDED_ENABLE_THINKING=false
